The paper deals with the problem of downlink precoding for a massive multiuser MIMO system, which involves signal processing, information theory, and communication networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the performance of linear and nonlinear precoders, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with the use of low-resolution digital-to-analog converters (DACs) at the base station, which is related to hardware and implementation issues and could be classified under cs.COM (Computer Architecture and Embedded Systems).
